{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775851428133,"sessionID":"ses_28701c770ffe7IF9hHkfCd4Qlx","part":{"id":"prt_d78fe58fa001ZQ5SFtAkKVEXV1","messageID":"msg_d78fe4c6f001zeAPWcowOuMiUb","sessionID":"ses_28701c770ffe7IF9hHkfCd4Qlx","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-c349c6a4e2c2444cad8ffd5c8026078e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/deployment/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/deployment/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deployment Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Deploy AgentCube control-plane components (Workload Manager, Router), optional Volcano agent scheduler, and required Redis connectivity via the `agentcube` Helm chart, container images, and Makefile-driven builds.\n5: \n6: ## Requirements\n7: \n8: ### Requirement: Helm chart installation\n9: The system SHALL support installing/upgrading the AgentCube stack with Helm from `manifests/charts/base`, including namespace creation and values for Redis, images, replicas, and optional router RBAC.\n10: \n11: #### Scenario: Install with release namespace\n12: - **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster and Helm 3 available\n13: - **WHEN** the operator runs `helm upgrade --install <release> manifests/charts/base --namespace <ns> --create-namespace` with required `redis.addr` (and optional `redis.password`) plus component image overrides as needed\n14: - **THEN** chart templates apply Workload Manager and Router workloads (and optional Volcano resources when enabled) in `<ns>` without manual editing of rendered YAML\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: Helm values and Redis connectivity\n17: The system SHALL require Redis address configuration for Workload Manager and Router at runtime via chart values `redis.addr` and `redis.password` (empty password permitted when Redis has no auth).\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: Components receive Redis env vars\n20: - **GIVEN** `redis.addr` and `redis.password` set in Helm values\n21: - **WHEN** pods for `workloadmanager` and `agentcube-router` start\n22: - **THEN** each container SHALL have environment variables `REDIS_ADDR` and `REDIS_PASSWORD` populated from those values\n23: \n24: ### Requirement: Workload Manager deployment shape\n25: The system SHALL deploy Workload Manager as a `Deployment` and `Service` named `workloadmanager` with replica count, container image, service type/port, resource requests/limits, health probes, and optional `extraEnv` driven from `values.yaml`.\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Default replica and service exposure\n28: - **GIVEN** default chart values\n29: - **WHEN** the chart is installed\n30: - **THEN** the Workload Manager `Deployment` SHALL use `workloadmanager.replicas` (default 1), expose HTTP on `workloadmanager.service.port` (default 8080), and use liveness/readiness HTTP GET `/health` on that port\n31: \n32: ### Requirement: Router deployment shape\n33: The system SHALL deploy the Router as a `Deployment` and `Service` named `agentcube-router` with replica count, image, `ClusterIP` service mapping `port`→`targetPort`, resource requests/limits, optional dedicated `serviceAccountName`, and `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` pointing at the in-cluster Workload Manager service.\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Router reaches Workload Manager by DNS\n36: - **GIVEN** release namespace `N` and Workload Manager service port `P` from values\n37: - **WHEN** the Router pod starts\n38: - **THEN** it SHALL have `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` set to `http://workloadmanager.N.svc.cluster.local:P` and container args including `--port=<targetPort>` and `--debug`\n39: \n40: ### Requirement: Workload Manager ClusterRole permissions\n41: The system SHALL create a `ServiceAccount` `workloadmanager`, a `ClusterRole` `workloadmanager`, and `ClusterRoleBinding` `workloadmanager` granting the rules required for agent-sandbox, AgentCube runtime CRDs, core workloads, auth, and secrets.\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: Binding ties SA to cluster role\n44: - **GIVEN** chart installation in namespace `N`\n45: - **WHEN** RBAC resources are applied\n46: - **THEN** subject `ServiceAccount/workloadmanager` in namespace `N` SHALL be bound to `ClusterRole/workloadmanager` via `ClusterRoleBinding/workloadmanager`\n47: \n48: ### Requirement: Optional Router namespace Role\n49: The system SHALL optionally create namespace-scoped `ServiceAccount`, `Role`, and `RoleBinding` for the Router when `router.rbac.create` is true, granting secret management in that namespace.\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: RBAC off by default\n52: - **GIVEN** `router.rbac.create: false`\n53: - **WHEN** the chart renders templates\n54: - **THEN** Router optional RBAC manifests SHALL NOT be emitted\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: RBAC on with named service account\n57: - **GIVEN** `router.rbac.create: true` and `router.serviceAccountName` set (or defaulted by template to `agentcube-router`)\n58: - **WHEN** the chart is applied\n59: - **THEN** Router pods MAY use that `serviceAccountName` and the Role SHALL allow verbs on `secrets` in the release namespace\n60: \n61: ### Requirement: Optional Volcano agent scheduler\n62: The system SHALL optionally deploy Volcano agent scheduler resources (ServiceAccount, ConfigMap, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding, Service, Deployment) when `volcano.scheduler.enabled` is true.\n63: \n64: #### Scenario: Scheduler disabled\n65: - **GIVEN** `volcano.scheduler.enabled: false` (default)\n66: - **WHEN** templates render\n67: - **THEN** no Volcano scheduler objects SHALL be created\n68: \n69: ### Requirement: CRDs shipped with the chart\n70: The system SHALL ship `CustomResourceDefinition` manifests for `agentruntimes` and `codeinterpreters` under the chart `crds/` directory so Helm installs them with the chart lifecycle.\n71: \n72: #### Scenario: CRD group and scope\n73: - **GIVEN** chart path `manifests/charts/base`\n74: - **WHEN** CRD YAML is applied\n75: - **THEN** both CRDs SHALL use API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`, version `v1alpha1`, and `scope: Namespaced`\n76: \n77: ### Requirement: Docker images for core binaries\n78: The system SHALL provide Dockerfiles to build three images: Workload Manager (`docker/Dockerfile`), Router (`docker/Dockerfile.router`), and picod (`docker/Dockerfile.picod`).\n79: \n80: #### Scenario: Multi-stage Go build for control plane\n81: - **GIVEN** repository root as build context\n82: - **WHEN** `docker build -f docker/Dockerfile` (or `Dockerfile.router`) runs\n83: - **THEN** the image SHALL compile the respective Go binary with `CGO_ENABLED=0` and run it from Alpine 3.19 as a non-root user (`apiserver` UID 1000 or `router` UID 1000) exposing port 8080\n84: \n85: ### Requirement: Makefile build targets\n86: The system SHALL expose Make targets to build binaries (`build`, related targets), run tests (`test`), build/push Docker images (`docker-*`), run code generation (`generate`, `gen-crd`, `gen-client`, `gen-all`, `gen-check`), and run E2E (`e2e`, `e2e-clean`).\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: Default `make` builds workload manager\n89: - **GIVEN** Go toolchain and generated code prerequisites\n90: - **WHEN** the operator runs `make` (default `all` → `build`)\n91: - **THEN** `bin/workloadmanager` SHALL be produced from `./cmd/workload-manager` after `generate`\n92: \n93: #### Scenario: E2E entrypoint\n94: - **GIVEN** Kind, kubectl, Docker, Helm, and curl available\n95: - **WHEN** the operator runs `make e2e`\n96: - **THEN** the repository SHALL execute `./test/e2e/run_e2e.sh` which provisions the cluster (unless skipped), deploys dependencies, and runs Go and Python E2E tests\n\n(End of file - total 96 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deployment Specification\n\n## Purpose\nDeploy AgentCube control-plane components (Workload Manager, Router), optional Volcano agent scheduler, and required Redis connectivity via the `agentcube` Helm chart, container images, and Makefile-driven builds.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Helm chart installation\nThe system SHALL support installing/upgrading the AgentCube stack with Helm from `manifests/charts/base`, including namespace creation and values for Redis, images, replicas, and optional router RBAC.\n\n#### Scenario: Install with release namespace\n- **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster and Helm 3 available\n- **WHEN** the operator runs `helm upgrade --install <release> manifests/charts/base --namespace <ns> --create-namespace` with required `redis.addr` (and optional `redis.password`) plus component image overrides as needed\n- **THEN** chart templates apply Workload Manager and Router workloads (and optional Volcano resources when enabled) in `<ns>` without manual editing of rendered YAML\n\n### Requirement: Helm values and Redis connectivity\nThe system SHALL require Redis address configuration for Workload Manager and Router at runtime via chart values `redis.addr` and `redis.password` (empty password permitted when Redis has no auth).\n\n#### Scenario: Components receive Redis env vars\n- **GIVEN** `redis.addr` and `redis.password` set in Helm values","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/deployment/spec.md","time":{"start":1775851428121,"end":1775851428132}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775851428136,"sessionID":"ses_28701c770ffe7IF9hHkfCd4Qlx","part":{"id":"prt_d78fe55400010NPl6weR8el31X","messageID":"msg_d78fe4c6f001zeAPWcowOuMiUb","sessionID":"ses_28701c770ffe7IF9hHkfCd4Qlx","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-32fa8954af0a4e31ab366cbb69ca49b9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-008/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-008/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-008 Delta Spec\n2: \n3: [To be filled]\n\n(End of file - total 3 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-008 Delta Spec\n\n[To be filled]","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-008/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775851428116,"end":1775851428135}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775851428139,"sessionID":"ses_28701c770ffe7IF9hHkfCd4Qlx","part":{"id":"prt_d78fe5727001S6HG9KSpkwxkVH","messageID":"msg_d78fe4c6f001zeAPWcowOuMiUb","sessionID":"ses_28701c770ffe7IF9hHkfCd4Qlx","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-86d783bd7acc440ca9558d17167b6f59","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/router/jwt.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/router/jwt.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: package router\n2: \n3: import (\n4: \t\"context\"\n5: \t\"crypto/rsa\"\n6: \t\"crypto/x509\"\n7: \t\"encoding/pem\"\n8: \t\"fmt\"\n9: \t\"time\"\n10: \n11: \t\"github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5\"\n12: \tcorev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n13: \tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n14: \t\"k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes\"\n15: \t\"k8s.io/klog/v2\"\n16: )\n17: \n18: const (\n19: \tprivateKeyPEMType  = \"RSA PRIVATE KEY\"\n20: \tpublicKeyPEMType   = \"PUBLIC KEY\"\n21: \tjwtTokenExpiration = 5 * time.Minute\n22: )\n23: \n24: type JWTManager struct {\n25: \tprivateKey *rsa.PrivateKey\n26: \tpublicKey  *rsa.PublicKey\n27: \tclientset  kubernetes.Interface\n28: \tnamespace  string\n29: }\n30: \n31: func NewJWTManager(clientset kubernetes.Interface, namespace string) (*JWTManager, error) {\n32: \tif clientset == nil {\n33: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"kubernetes clientset is required\")\n34: \t}\n35: \n36: \tif namespace == \"\" {\n37: \t\tnamespace = defaultNamespace\n38: \t}\n39: \n40: \tjwtMgr := &JWTManager{\n41: \t\tclientset: clientset,\n42: \t\tnamespace: namespace,\n43: \t}\n44: \n45: \tif err := jwtMgr.tryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(); err != nil {\n46: \t\tklog.Warningf(\"Failed to load or store JWT key secret: %v. Generating in-memory keys only.\", err)\n47: \t\tprivateKey, publicKey, err := generateRSAKeyPair()\n48: \t\tif err != nil {\n49: \t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to generate RSA key pair: %w\", err)\n50: \t\t}\n51: \t\tjwtMgr.privateKey = privateKey\n52: \t\tjwtMgr.publicKey = publicKey\n53: \t}\n54: \n55: \treturn jwtMgr, nil\n56: }\n57: \n58: func (j *JWTManager) GenerateToken(sessionID string) (string, error) {\n59: \tif j.privateKey == nil {\n60: \t\treturn \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"JWT manager not initialized with private key\")\n61: \t}\n62: \n63: \tnow := time.Now()\n64: \tclaims := &JWTClaims{\n65: \t\tSessionID: sessionID,\n66: \t\tRegisteredClaims: jwt.RegisteredClaims{\n67: \t\t\tIssuedAt:  jwt.NewNumericDate(now),\n68: \t\t\tExpiresAt: jwt.NewNumericDate(now.Add(jwtTokenExpiration)),\n69: \t\t\tNotBefore: jwt.NewNumericDate(now),\n70: \t\t},\n71: \t}\n72: \n73: \ttoken := jwt.NewWithClaims(jwt.SigningMethodRS256, claims)\n74: \ttokenString, err := token.SignedString(j.privateKey)\n75: \tif err != nil {\n76: \t\treturn \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"failed to sign JWT token: %w\", err)\n77: \t}\n78: \n79: \treturn tokenString, nil\n80: }\n81: \n82: func (j *JWTManager) ValidateToken(tokenString string) (*JWTClaims, error) {\n83: \tif j.publicKey == nil {\n84: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"JWT manager not initialized with public key\")\n85: \t}\n86: \n87: \ttoken, err := jwt.ParseWithClaims(tokenString, &JWTClaims{}, func(token *jwt.Token) (interface{}, error) {\n88: \t\tif _, ok := token.Method.(*jwt.SigningMethodRSA); !ok {\n89: \t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"unexpected signing method: %v\", token.Header[\"alg\"])\n90: \t\t}\n91: \t\treturn j.publicKey, nil\n92: \t})\n93: \n94: \tif err != nil {\n95: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to parse JWT token: %w\", err)\n96: \t}\n97: \n98: \tclaims, ok := token.Claims.(*JWTClaims)\n99: \tif !ok || !token.Valid {\n100: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"invalid JWT token claims\")\n101: \t}\n102: \n103: \tif time.Now().After(claims.ExpiresAt.Time) {\n104: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"JWT token has expired\")\n105: \t}\n106: \n107: \treturn claims, nil\n108: }\n109: \n110: func (j *JWTManager) tryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret() error {\n111: \tsecret, err := j.clientset.CoreV1().Secrets(j.namespace).Get(j.context(), secretName, metav1.GetOptions{})\n112: \tif err == nil {\n113: \t\treturn j.loadKeysFromSecret(secret)\n114: \t}\n115: \n116: \tif err != nil && !isNotFoundError(err) {\n117: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to check for existing JWT secret: %w\", err)\n118: \t}\n119: \n120: \treturn j.storeJWTKeySecret()\n121: }\n122: \n123: func (j *JWTManager) loadKeysFromSecret(secret *corev1.Secret) error {\n124: \tprivateKeyPEM, ok := secret.Data[\"private.pem\"]\n125: \tif !ok {\n126: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"secret does not contain private.pem\")\n127: \t}\n128: \n129: \tpublicKeyPEM, ok := secret.Data[\"public.pem\"]\n130: \tif !ok {\n131: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"secret does not contain public.pem\")\n132: \t}\n133: \n134: \tprivateKey, err := parsePrivateKeyPEM(privateKeyPEM)\n135: \tif err != nil {\n136: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to parse private key: %w\", err)\n137: \t}\n138: \n139: \tpublicKey, err := parsePublicKeyPEM(publicKeyPEM)\n140: \tif err != nil {\n141: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to parse public key: %w\", err)\n142: \t}\n143: \n144: \tj.privateKey = privateKey\n145: \tj.publicKey = publicKey\n146: \n147: \tklog.Infof(\"Successfully loaded JWT keys from secret: %s\", secretName)\n148: \treturn nil\n149: }\n150: \n151: func (j *JWTManager) storeJWTKeySecret() error {\n152: \tprivateKey, publicKey, err := generateRSAKeyPair()\n153: \tif err != nil {\n154: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to generate RSA key pair: %w\", err)\n155: \t}\n156: \n157: \tprivateKeyPEM := pem.EncodeToMemory(&pem.Block{\n158: \t\tType:  privateKeyPEMType,\n159: \t\tBytes: x509.MarshalPKCS1PrivateKey(privateKey),\n160: \t})\n161: \n162: \tpublicKeyBytes, err := x509.MarshalPKIXPublicKey(publicKey)\n163: \tif err != nil {\n164: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to marshal public key: %w\", err)\n165: \t}\n166: \n167: \tpublicKeyPEM := pem.EncodeToMemory(&pem.Block{\n168: \t\tType:  publicKeyPEMType,\n169: \t\tBytes: publicKeyBytes,\n170: \t})\n171: \n172: \tsecret := &corev1.Secret{\n173: \t\tObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n174: \t\t\tName:      secretName,\n175: \t\t\tNamespace: j.namespace,\n176: \t\t},\n177: \t\tData: map[string][]byte{\n178: \t\t\t\"private.pem\": privateKeyPEM,\n179: \t\t\t\"public.pem\":  publicKeyPEM,\n180: \t\t},\n181: \t}\n182: \n183: \t_, err = j.clientset.CoreV1().Secrets(j.namespace).Create(j.context(), secret, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n184: \tif err != nil {\n185: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create JWT key secret: %w\", err)\n186: \t}\n187: \n188: \tj.privateKey = privateKey\n189: \tj.publicKey = publicKey\n190: \n191: \tklog.Infof(\"Successfully created JWT key secret: %s\", secretName)\n192: \treturn nil\n193: }\n194: \n195: func (j *JWTManager) context() context.Context {\n196: \treturn context.Background()\n197: }\n198: \n199: func generateRSAKeyPair() (*rsa.PrivateKey, *rsa.PublicKey, error) {\n200: \tprivateKey, err := rsa.GenerateKey(nil, 2048)\n201: \tif err != nil {\n202: \t\treturn nil, nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to generate RSA key: %w\", err)\n203: \t}\n204: \n205: \treturn privateKey, &privateKey.PublicKey, nil\n206: }\n207: \n208: func parsePrivateKeyPEM(privateKeyPEM []byte) (*rsa.PrivateKey, error) {\n209: \tblock, _ := pem.Decode(privateKeyPEM)\n210: \tif block == nil {\n211: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to decode PEM block\")\n212: \t}\n213: \n214: \tif block.Type != privateKeyPEMType {\n215: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"invalid PEM block type: %s\", block.Type)\n216: \t}\n217: \n218: \tprivateKey, err := x509.ParsePKCS1PrivateKey(block.Bytes)\n219: \tif err != nil {\n220: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to parse private key: %w\", err)\n221: \t}\n222: \n223: \treturn privateKey, nil\n224: }\n225: \n226: func parsePublicKeyPEM(publicKeyPEM []byte) (*rsa.PublicKey, error) {\n227: \tblock, _ := pem.Decode(publicKeyPEM)\n228: \tif block == nil {\n229: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to decode PEM block\")\n230: \t}\n231: \n232: \tif block.Type != publicKeyPEMType {\n233: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"invalid PEM block type: %s\", block.Type)\n234: \t}\n235: \n236: \tpublicKey, err := x509.ParsePKIXPublicKey(block.Bytes)\n237: \tif err != nil {\n238: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to parse public key: %w\", err)\n239: \t}\n240: \n241: \trsaPublicKey, ok := publicKey.(*rsa.PublicKey)\n242: \tif !ok {\n243: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"not an RSA public key\")\n244: \t}\n245: \n246: \treturn rsaPublicKey, nil\n247: }\n248: \n249: func isNotFoundError(err error) bool {\n250: \treturn false\n251: }\n\n(End of file - total 251 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"package router\n\nimport (\n\t\"context\"\n\t\"crypto/rsa\"\n\t\"crypto/x509\"\n\t\"encoding/pem\"\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"time\"\n\n\t\"github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5\"\n\tcorev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n\tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n\t\"k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes\"\n\t\"k8s.io/klog/v2\"\n)\n\nconst (\n\tprivateKeyPEMType  = \"RSA PRIVATE KEY\"\n\tpublicKeyPEMType   = \"PUBLIC KEY\"","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/router/jwt.go","time":{"start":1775851428119,"end":1775851428137}}}}
