{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775851433378,"sessionID":"ses_28701c770ffe7IF9hHkfCd4Qlx","part":{"id":"prt_d78fe6b7f001BiX6gK2ZD6ILpm","messageID":"msg_d78fe5970001ThGU05VoT5XvvF","sessionID":"ses_28701c770ffe7IF9hHkfCd4Qlx","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-9c1876c279bc48fdbaa397708ae95103","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-002/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-002/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-002 Delta Specification: CRD CodeInterpreter 类型定义\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Define Go type definitions and Kubernetes CRD registration for the `CodeInterpreter` custom resource in the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group, including integration with the generated client-go library and proper API machinery support.\n6: \n7: ## Requirements\n8: \n9: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreter type metadata and API group version\n10: \n11: The system SHALL define `CodeInterpreter` as a Kubernetes custom resource with `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` API group, `v1alpha1` version, kind `CodeInterpreter`, and resource plural `codeinterpreters`.\n12: \n13: #### Scenario: Type metadata reflects GVR mapping\n14: - **GIVEN** a Kubernetes API server resolving the CRD type\n15: - **WHEN** the `TypeMeta` fields are inspected\n16: - **THEN** `APIVersion` is `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` and `Kind` is `CodeInterpreter`\n17: \n18: #### Scenario: Resource plural matches client-go expectations\n19: - **GIVEN** a typed client for `CodeInterpreter`\n20: - **WHEN** constructing a `GroupVersionResource` from the type\n21: - **THEN** resource name is `codeinterpreters` in plural form\n22: \n23: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterSpec structure with required fields\n24: \n25: The system SHALL define `CodeInterpreterSpec` struct with required fields: `Image` of type `string` for the interpreter container image, and `Runtime` of type `string` for specifying the execution environment (e.g., \"python\", \"javascript\").\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Spec requires image\n28: - **GIVEN** a new `CodeInterpreter` object being created\n29: - **WHEN** the spec is populated\n30: - **THEN** `Image` must be non-empty and contains a valid container image reference\n31: \n32: #### Scenario: Runtime field specifies execution environment\n33: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreter` with a configured runtime\n34: - **WHEN** the spec is serialized to YAML\n35: - **THEN** `Runtime` contains a valid runtime identifier string\n36: \n37: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterSpec with optional configuration fields\n38: \n39: The system SHALL define `CodeInterpreterSpec` with optional fields: `Resources` of type `*SandboxContainerResources` for resource limits/requests, `Timeout` of type `*metav1.Duration` for execution timeout, `Env` of type `[]SandboxEnvVar` for environment variables, and `EnabledPackages` of type `[]string` for allowed Python/JS packages.\n40: \n41: #### Scenario: Optional resources field provides constraints\n42: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreter` with resource limits defined\n43: - **WHEN** the interpreter container is created\n44: - **THEN** the container is configured with the specified CPU and memory constraints\n45: \n46: #### Scenario: Timeout field limits execution duration\n47: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreter` with `Timeout` set to `5m`\n48: - **WHEN** a code execution exceeds 5 minutes\n49: - **THEN** the execution is terminated with a timeout error\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: Environment variables are injected\n52: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreter` with environment variables defined\n53: - **WHEN** the interpreter container starts\n54: - **THEN** the specified environment variables are available in the execution context\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: Package filtering restricts available libraries\n57: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreter` with `EnabledPackages` set to `[\"numpy\", \"pandas\"]`\n58: - **WHEN** code attempts to import `tensorflow`\n59: - **THEN** the import is blocked and an error is returned\n60: \n61: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterStatus with conditions support\n62: \n63: The system SHALL define `CodeInterpreterStatus` struct with optional `Conditions` field of type `[]metav1.Condition` for tracking interpreter state transitions, and `Ready` field of type `bool` to indicate if the interpreter is ready to execute code.\n64: \n65: #### Scenario: Status conditions are optional\n66: - **GIVEN** a newly created `CodeInterpreter` resource\n67: - **WHEN** status is initially empty\n68: - **THEN** resource creation succeeds without requiring conditions\n69: \n70: #### Scenario: Ready field reflects operational state\n71: - **GIVEN** a controller managing `CodeInterpreter` lifecycle\n72: - **WHEN** the interpreter container becomes ready\n73: - **THEN** `Ready` is set to `true` in the status\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: Condition updates follow Kubernetes conventions\n76: - **GIVEN** a controller managing `CodeInterpreter` lifecycle\n77: - **WHEN** transitioning between states (e.g., Provisioning → Ready)\n78: - **THEN** conditions are added with appropriate types, reasons, and transition timestamps\n79: \n80: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterList type for collection operations\n81: \n82: The system SHALL define `CodeInterpreterList` as a standard Kubernetes list type containing `[]CodeInterpreter` items and standard list metadata.\n83: \n84: #### Scenario: List type supports pagination\n85: - **GIVEN** multiple `CodeInterpreter` resources in a namespace\n86: - **WHEN** `List` operation is called with `ListOptions.Limit`\n87: - **THEN** response returns a `CodeInterpreterList` with `Continue` token when more items exist\n88: \n89: ### Requirement: Scheme registration for serialization\n90: \n91: The system SHALL register `CodeInterpreter` and `CodeInterpreterList` types in the Kubernetes scheme for proper JSON/YAML serialization and deserialization.\n92: \n93: #### Scenario: YAML deserialization produces correct Go types\n94: - **GIVEN** a YAML file containing `kind: CodeInterpreter` in the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group\n95: - **WHEN** the YAML is decoded using the registered scheme\n96: - **THEN** a `CodeInterpreter` struct instance is created with correct field mappings\n97: \n98: #### Scenario: List kind maps to CodeInterpreterList\n99: - **GIVEN** a YAML file containing `kind: CodeInterpreterList`\n100: - **WHEN** the YAML is decoded\n101: - **THEN** a `CodeInterpreterList` struct instance is created with items as `[]CodeInterpreter`\n102: \n103: ### Requirement: CRD subresources support\n104: \n105: The system SHALL enable status subresource on `CodeInterpreter` to allow independent updates to status without modifying spec.\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: Status update does not modify spec\n108: - **GIVEN** an existing `CodeInterpreter` with both spec and status\n109: - **WHEN** a status-only update is performed via API server\n110: - **THEN** only status fields change and spec remains unmodified\n111: \n112: #### Scenario: Status and spec have independent versioning\n113: - **GIVEN** a controller updating status\n114: - **WHEN** status changes multiple times\n115: - **THEN** each status update increments `metadata.generation` independently of spec modifications\n116: \n117: ### Requirement: Default values for spec fields\n118: \n119: The system SHALL define kubebuilder markers to set default values: `Timeout` defaults to `\"5m\"` and `Runtime` defaults to `\"python\"`.\n120: \n121: #### Scenario: Missing timeout field receives default\n122: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreter` created without explicit timeout value\n123: - **WHEN** the resource is created via API\n124: - **THEN** `Timeout` is set to `5m` automatically\n125: \n126: #### Scenario: Missing runtime field receives default\n127: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreter` created without explicit runtime value\n128: - **WHEN** the resource is created via API\n129: - **THEN** `Runtime` is set to `\"python\"` automatically\n130: \n131: #### Scenario: Explicit values override defaults\n132: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreter` created with custom timeout and runtime values\n133: - **WHEN** the resource is created\n134: - **THEN** the explicit values are preserved and defaults are not applied\n135: \n136: ### Requirement: OpenAPI validation for spec fields\n137: \n138: The system SHALL generate OpenAPI v3 schema for `CodeInterpreter` to enable validation of field types, required fields, and constraints.\n139: \n140: #### Scenario: Required field validation\n141: - **GIVEN** a request creating `CodeInterpreter` without required `Image`\n142: - **WHEN** the API server validates the request\n143: - **THEN** validation fails with error indicating `image` is required\n144: \n145: #### Scenario: Runtime field validates against allowed values\n146: - **GIVEN** a request creating `CodeInterpreter` with invalid runtime value\n147: - **WHEN** the API server validates the request\n148: - **THEN** validation fails with error about invalid runtime value\n149: \n150: #### Scenario: Timeout field validates duration format\n151: - **GIVEN** a request creating `CodeInterpreter` with invalid duration format\n152: - **WHEN** the API server validates the request\n153: - **THEN** validation fails with error about invalid duration format\n154: \n155: ### Requirement: Print columns for kubectl readability\n156: \n157: The system SHALL configure additional printer columns for `kubectl get` output, including `Ready` derived from `status.ready`, `Runtime` derived from `spec.runtime`, and `Age` derived from `metadata.creationTimestamp`.\n158: \n159: #### Scenario: Ready column displays correctly\n160: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreter` resource with `Ready` set to `true`\n161: - **WHEN** `kubectl get codeinterpreters` is executed\n162: - **THEN** the Ready column shows `True`\n163: \n164: #### Scenario: Runtime column displays configured runtime\n165: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreter` resource with `Runtime` set to `\"python\"`\n166: - **WHEN** `kubectl get codeinterpreters` is executed\n167: - **THEN** the Runtime column shows `python`\n168: \n169: #### Scenario: Age column displays correctly\n170: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreter` resource that was created 10 minutes ago\n171: - **WHEN** `kubectl get codeinterpreters` is executed\n172: - **THEN** the Age column shows `10m` or equivalent time duration\n173: \n174: ### Requirement: CRD status storage optimization\n175: \n176: The system SHALL use status subresource to ensure status updates are stored efficiently and do not trigger spec reconciliation unnecessarily.\n177: \n178: #### Scenario: Frequent status updates\n179: - **GIVEN** a controller updating `CodeInterpreter` status every 30 seconds\n180: - **WHEN** multiple status updates occur\n181: - **THEN** each update only writes to status subresource and does not trigger full reconciliation\n182: \n183: ### Requirement: Type registration in code-generation\n184: \n185: The system SHALL ensure `CodeInterpreter` types are included in the client-go code-generation pipeline to produce typed clients, informers, and listers.\n186: \n187: #### Scenario: Typed client operations work\n188: - **GIVEN** a `Clientset` instance from generated client-go code\n189: - **WHEN** calling `client.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(namespace).Create`\n190: - **THEN** the operation succeeds with proper type safety and returns a `CodeInterpreter` pointer\n191: \n192: #### Scenario: Informer factory recognizes CodeInterpreter\n193: - **GIVEN** a `SharedInformerFactory` for the runtime API group\n194: - **WHEN** `Runtime().V1alpha1().CodeInterpreters().Informer()` is called\n195: - **THEN** an informer watching `codeinterpreters` resources is returned\n196: \n197: ### Requirement: JSON tag naming convention\n198: \n199: The system SHALL use camelCase JSON tags for all fields to match Kubernetes API conventions and client-go expectations.\n200: \n201: #### Scenario: JSON serialization uses camelCase\n202: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreter` struct populated with Go fields\n203: - **WHEN** serialized to JSON\n204: - **THEN** the JSON keys are camelCase (e.g., `image`, `runtime`, `timeout`, `resources`)\n205: \n206: ### Requirement: DeepCopy methods for safety\n207: \n208: The system SHALL implement `DeepCopy`, `DeepCopyInto`, `DeepCopyObject` methods for `CodeInterpreter` to support safe copying in controllers.\n209: \n210: #### Scenario: DeepCopy creates independent instance\n211: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreter` instance with populated fields\n212: - **WHEN** `DeepCopy` is called\n213: - **THEN** the returned copy is independent and modifications to the copy do not affect the original\n214: \n215: ### Requirement: Validation markers for fields\n216: \n217: The system SHALL use kubebuilder validation markers to enforce constraints on spec fields where applicable.\n218: \n219: #### Scenario: Image field validates format\n220: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreter` with `Image` set to invalid format\n221: - **WHEN** the resource is submitted to the API server\n222: - **THEN** validation fails with error indicating invalid image format\n223: \n224: #### Scenario: Timeout field validates minimum duration\n225: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreter` with `Timeout` set to `\"1s\"`\n226: - **WHEN** the resource is submitted to the API server\n227: - **THEN** validation passes as the timeout is at minimum allowed duration\n228: \n229: ### Requirement: Label selector support for listing\n230: \n231: The system SHALL support standard Kubernetes label selectors when listing `CodeInterpreter` resources.\n232: \n233: #### Scenario: Label selector filters results\n234: - **GIVEN** multiple `CodeInterpreter` resources with different labels\n235: - **WHEN** `List` is called with a label selector matching a specific label\n236: - **THEN** only resources matching the selector are returned\n237: \n238: ### Requirement: Watch support for controller integration\n239: \n240: The system SHALL support watch operations on `CodeInterpreter` resources to enable controllers to react to changes efficiently.\n241: \n242: #### Scenario: Watch events notify of changes\n243: - **GIVEN** a watch stream established on `CodeInterpreter` resources\n244: - **WHEN** a new `CodeInterpreter` is created\n245: - **THEN** the watch stream receives an ADDED event with the new resource\n246: \n247: ### Requirement: Runtime validation for supported languages\n248: \n249: The system SHALL validate that the `Runtime` field contains one of the supported execution environments: `\"python\"`, `\"javascript\"`, `\"typescript\"`, or `\"go\"`.\n250: \n251: #### Scenario: Valid runtime values are accepted\n252: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreter` with `Runtime` set to `\"python\"`\n253: - **WHEN** the resource is created\n254: - **THEN** creation succeeds without validation errors\n255: \n256: #### Scenario: Invalid runtime values are rejected\n257: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreter` with `Runtime` set to `\"ruby\"`\n258: - **WHEN** the resource is submitted to the API server\n259: - **THEN** validation fails with error indicating unsupported runtime\n260: \n261: ### Requirement: Package validation for security\n262: \n263: The system SHALL validate that packages listed in `EnabledPackages` follow naming conventions and do not contain malicious patterns.\n264: \n265: #### Scenario: Valid package names are accepted\n266: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreter` with `EnabledPackages` set to `[\"numpy\", \"pandas\"]`\n267: - **WHEN** the resource is created\n268: - **THEN** creation succeeds without validation errors\n269: \n270: #### Scenario: Invalid package names are rejected\n271: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreter` with `EnabledPackages` set to `[\"../../../etc/passwd\"]`\n272: - **WHEN** the resource is submitted to the API server\n273: - **THEN** validation fails with error about invalid package name\n274: \n275: ### Requirement: Namespace-scoped resource\n276: \n277: The system SHALL define `CodeInterpreter` as a namespace-scoped resource (not cluster-scoped) to allow multiple interpreters per namespace.\n278: \n279: #### Scenario: Resource exists in namespace scope\n280: - **GIVEN** two namespaces `dev` and `prod`\n281: - **WHEN** creating a `CodeInterpreter` named `main` in each namespace\n282: - **THEN** both resources can exist independently with the same name\n283: \n284: #### Scenario: List operations respect namespace\n285: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreter` resources in multiple namespaces\n286: - **WHEN** `List` is called without namespace specified\n287: - **THEN** only resources in the configured namespace are returned\n288: \n289: ### Requirement: Finalizers for cleanup\n290: \n291: The system SHALL support finalizers on `CodeInterpreter` to ensure proper cleanup of associated resources (pods, PVCs, etc.) before deletion.\n292: \n293: #### Scenario: Finalizer prevents immediate deletion\n294: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreter` with active pods and a finalizer\n295: - **WHEN** a delete request is issued\n296: - **THEN** the resource is marked for deletion but not removed until the finalizer is removed\n297: \n298: #### Scenario: Finalizer enables graceful cleanup\n299: - **GIVEN** a controller managing `CodeInterpreter` resources\n300: - **WHEN** deletion is detected and cleanup is complete\n301: - **THEN** the controller removes the finalizer and the resource is garbage collected\n\n(End of file - total 301 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-002 Delta Specification: CRD CodeInterpreter 类型定义\n\n## Purpose\n\nDefine Go type definitions and Kubernetes CRD registration for the `CodeInterpreter` custom resource in the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group, including integration with the generated client-go library and proper API machinery support.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreter type metadata and API group version\n\nThe system SHALL define `CodeInterpreter` as a Kubernetes custom resource with `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` API group, `v1alpha1` version, kind `CodeInterpreter`, and resource plural `codeinterpreters`.\n\n#### Scenario: Type metadata reflects GVR mapping\n- **GIVEN** a Kubernetes API server resolving the CRD type\n- **WHEN** the `TypeMeta` fields are inspected\n- **THEN** `APIVersion` is `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` and `Kind` is `CodeInterpreter`\n\n#### Scenario: Resource plural matches client-go expectations\n- **GIVEN** a typed client for `CodeInterpreter`\n- **WHEN** constructing a `GroupVersionResource` from the type","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-002/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775851433367,"end":1775851433376}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775851433381,"sessionID":"ses_28701c770ffe7IF9hHkfCd4Qlx","part":{"id":"prt_d78fe6d7d001X5EBlFDb8jjJ5m","messageID":"msg_d78fe5970001ThGU05VoT5XvvF","sessionID":"ses_28701c770ffe7IF9hHkfCd4Qlx","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-143afc17d5f0470d87455a386b3b2669","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/router/types.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/router/types.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: package router\n2: \n3: import (\n4: \t\"time\"\n5: \n6: \t\"github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5\"\n7: \n8: \t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n9: )\n10: \n11: type JWTClaims struct {\n12: \tSessionID string `json:\"session_id\"`\n13: \tjwt.RegisteredClaims\n14: }\n15: \n16: type ErrorResponse struct {\n17: \tError string `json:\"error\"`\n18: \tCode  string `json:\"code,omitempty\"`\n19: }\n20: \n21: type GetSandboxBySessionRequest struct {\n22: \tSessionID string\n23: \tName      string\n24: \tNamespace string\n25: \tKind      string\n26: }\n27: \n28: type CreateSessionRequest struct {\n29: \tName      string\n30: \tNamespace string\n31: \tKind      string\n32: }\n33: \n34: type WorkloadManagerCreateRequest struct {\n35: \tKind      string `json:\"kind\"`\n36: \tName      string `json:\"name\"`\n37: \tNamespace string `json:\"namespace\"`\n38: }\n39: \n40: type WorkloadManagerCreateResponse struct {\n41: \tSessionID   string                    `json:\"sessionId\"`\n42: \tSandboxID   string                    `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n43: \tSandboxName string                    `json:\"sandboxName\"`\n44: \tEntryPoints []types.SandboxEntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n45: }\n46: \n47: type WorkloadManagerGetSessionRequest struct {\n48: \tSessionID string `uri:\"sessionId\" binding:\"required\"`\n49: }\n50: \n51: type WorkloadManagerGetSessionResponse struct {\n52: \tSessionID    string                    `json:\"sessionId\"`\n53: \tSandboxID    string                    `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n54: \tSandboxName  string                    `json:\"sandboxName\"`\n55: \tKind         string                    `json:\"kind\"`\n56: \tNamespace    string                    `json:\"namespace\"`\n57: \tName         string                    `json:\"name\"`\n58: \tEntryPoints  []types.SandboxEntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n59: \tLastActivity string                    `json:\"lastActivity\"`\n60: \tCreatedAt    string                    `json:\"createdAt\"`\n61: \tExpiresAt    string                    `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n62: \tPodIP        string                    `json:\"podIp,omitempty\"`\n63: }\n64: \n65: func SandboxInfoFromWorkloadManager(resp *WorkloadManagerGetSessionResponse, sessionID string) *types.SandboxInfo {\n66: \tcreatedAt, _ := time.Parse(time.RFC3339, resp.CreatedAt)\n67: \texpiresAt, _ := time.Parse(time.RFC3339, resp.ExpiresAt)\n68: \tlastActivity, _ := time.Parse(time.RFC3339, resp.LastActivity)\n69: \n70: \treturn &types.SandboxInfo{\n71: \t\tKind:             resp.Kind,\n72: \t\tSandboxID:        resp.SandboxID,\n73: \t\tSandboxName:      resp.SandboxName,\n74: \t\tSandboxNamespace: resp.Namespace,\n75: \t\tName:             resp.Name,\n76: \t\tEntryPoints:      resp.EntryPoints,\n77: \t\tSessionID:        sessionID,\n78: \t\tCreatedAt:        createdAt,\n79: \t\tExpiresAt:        expiresAt,\n80: \t\tStatus:           \"Ready\",\n81: \t\tPodIP:            resp.PodIP,\n82: \t\tNamespace:        resp.Namespace,\n83: \t\tLastActivityAt:   lastActivity,\n84: \t}\n85: }\n86: \n87: func NewErrorResponse(errorMsg string, code string) *ErrorResponse {\n88: \treturn &ErrorResponse{\n89: \t\tError: errorMsg,\n90: \t\tCode:  code,\n91: \t}\n92: }\n\n(End of file - total 92 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"package router\n\nimport (\n\t\"time\"\n\n\t\"github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5\"\n\n\t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n)\n\ntype JWTClaims struct {\n\tSessionID string `json:\"session_id\"`\n\tjwt.RegisteredClaims\n}\n\ntype ErrorResponse struct {\n\tError string `json:\"error\"`\n\tCode  string `json:\"code,omitempty\"`\n}\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/router/types.go","time":{"start":1775851433369,"end":1775851433379}}}}
